('Garlic Shrimp Bacon Alfredo',100,4,'In a large pot, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy.,Add the shrimp, salt, and pepper and cook until the shrimp is pink and opaque. Remove the shrimp and bacon from the pot, leaving any fat from cooking the bacon behind.,Add the onions, tomatoes, and garlic to the pot and cook until the garlic is starting to brown.,Add the cream and bring to a boil.,Once the cream is boiling, add the fettuccine. Return the shrimp and bacon to the pan, along with the Parmesan cheese and parsley. Stir until the cheese melts and the sauce coats the shrimp and pasta nicely.,Nutrition  Calories: 2185 Fat: 125 grams  Carbs: 192 grams Fiber: 9 grams  Sugars: 20 grams  Protein: 103 grams,Enjoy!,','When in doubt for dinner? Make fish! Recipes like <a href=\"https://tasty.co/recipe/tomato-pesto-salmon>tomato pesto salmon</a> and are colorful, versatile, and rich in protein. The best part is all of these dishes taste impressive but are actually super simple to prepare. Pair them with plenty of vegetables or your grain of choice, then sit back and enjoy.','https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/274143.jpg','protein:51;fat:62;calories:1086;sugar:9;carbs:94;fiber:4',1565),
('Tomato Basil Bruschetta',100,2,'Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C).,Slice the baguette into ½-inch (1 cm) rounds and place on a baking sheet.,Brush both sides of the baguette slices with olive oil.,Bake for for 6 minutes until slightly crispy.,In a medium bowl, combine the tomatoes, minced garlic, balsamic vinegar, basil, salt, and pepper.,Rub the garlic into one side of the baguette slices, then spoon the tomato mixture evenly across the slices.,Enjoy!,','The tomato plant is the most popularly cultivated plant around the world, grown in gardens, on farms, and in greenhouses. It is also an oft-overlooked ingredient in many food recipes. Well, not anymore! We are putting the spotlight on the tomato. And what better way to do so than to try out <a href=\"https://tasty.co/recipe/tomato-basil-soup\"> Tomato Basil Soup</a> or href=\"https://tasty.co/recipe/easy-tomato-basil-pasta-bake\"> Easy Tomato Basil Pasta Bake </a>? So what are you waiting for? Give the tomato the love it deserves! ','https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/413751.jpg','protein:18;fat:30;calories:681;sugar:12;carbs:86;fiber:5',1566),
('Healthy Cauliflower Parmesan Tots',100,3,'Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).,Grate the cauliflower with a coarse cheese grater.,Transfer the grated bits to a medium bowl and season with a ¼ teaspoon of the salt. Mix the cauliflower until well incorporated.,Let the cauliflower sit for 20 minutes until the salt has drawn out some of the moisture.,Pour the cauliflower into a kitchen towel and twist to strain as much liquid as you can.,Place the grated cauliflower back into a bowl and mix with the breadcrumbs, parsley, parmesan, garlic, remaining ¼ teaspoon of salt, pepper, and egg, and mix until well combined.,From the mixutre into 15 even sized tots and transfer to a parchment lined baking sheet.,Bake for 20-24 minutes, flipping each halfway through.,Serve with your choice of dipping sauce.,Enjoy!,',NULL,'https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/263779.jpg','protein:14;fat:6;calories:189;sugar:5;carbs:20;fiber:4',1571),
('Garlic Bread Bruschetta',100,2,'Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C).,In the microwave, melt the 3 tablespoons of butter with 1 clove of garlic.,Slice up a loaf of Italian bread to about 1-inch (2 ½ cm) thickness.,Top with melted garlic butter, Italian seasoning, and parmesan cheese.,Bake for approximately 15 minutes or until golden brown.,In a mixing bowl, combine the tomatoes, garlic, salt, pepper, basil, and olive oil and stir until everything is fully coated with olive oil.,Top the garlic bread with desired amount of tomato mixture.,Garnish with parmesan cheese.,Enjoy!,','Italian food is hands down among of the best of the world! And a wedding is the perfect time to feast on all the delicacies the cuisine has to offer, starting with  <a href=\"https://tasty.co/recipe/garlic-bread-bruschetta\">Garlic Bread Bruschetta</a> and moving towards  <a href=\"https://tasty.co/recipe/chicken-alfredo-ravioli-lasagna\">Chicken Alfredo Ravioli Lasagna</a>. End your meal with a few scoops of  <a href=\"https://tasty.co/recipe/fruit-wine-sorbet\">Fruit and Wine Sorbet</a> for a sweet, spiked finish.','https://s3.amazonaws.com/video-api-prod/assets/45b6d519020846398aed5718358f7b09/Italian_wedding_new.jpg','protein:21;fat:31;calories:812;sugar:21;carbs:112;fiber:10',1573),
('Vegan Mint Cookies',100,5,'In a small mixing bowl, combine chocolate chips, mint extract, and vegetable shortening, and microwave for 1 minute. Stir often and make sure the chocolate doesn\'t burn.,Dip cracker in chocolate mixture.,Place chocolate covered crackers on parchment-lined baking sheet. Refrigerate or freeze until hard.,Refrigerate or freeze until hard.,Enjoy!,','What’s a better palate cleanser than fresh mint? Aside from being a refreshing garnish to elevate your dishes, mint also works as a great antioxidant and has countless medicinal properties! From cakes to cocktails, it’s enhancing them all. Munch on some vibrant <a href=\"https://tasty.co/recipe/vegan-mint-cookies\">Vegan Mint Cookies</a> with a refreshing glass of <a href=\"https://tasty.co/recipe/invigorating-cucumber-mint-cocktail\">Cucumber Mint Cocktail</a>. Don’t forget to end your meal with a slice of <a href=\"https://tasty.co/recipe/mint-chocolate-cookie-dome-cake\">Mint Chocolate Chip Cookie Dome Cake</a>!','https://s3.amazonaws.com/video-api-prod/assets/2dccda7c5bd54e8e8a7462e11f0a101d/MintFB1.jpg','protein:3;fat:21;calories:278;sugar:11;carbs:24;fiber:3',1576),
('Truffle Mac ‘n’ Cheese',100,3,'Melt 1 tablespoon of butter in a medium pot over medium heat. Add the mushrooms, salt, and pepper and cook until the mushrooms are softened. Remove from the pot.,Add the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter and the flour to the pot. Whisk until the flour is toasted, approximately 2 minutes.,Add the milk while whisking continuously to avoid lumps. Cook until the sauce is thickened.,Whisk in the Parmesan and cheddar cheeses and season with salt and pepper.,Add the cooked pasta and mushrooms. Mix until the sauce coats the pasta well.,Top with truffle oil and chives.,Enjoy!,',NULL,'https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/267671.jpg','protein:38;fat:37;calories:872;sugar:7;carbs:94;fiber:3',1581),
('Muffin Tin Deviled Eggs',100,12,'Crack twelve eggs, and separate the yolks and egg whites into separate bowls.,Preheat oven to 300°F (150°C).,Spray a mini muffin tin with nonstick spray. Pour each yolk and egg white into its own mini muffin tin hole.,Place the tin into a baking dish with a tinfoil ring, wire wrack, or a towel to keep the muffin tin from touching the bottom of the baking dish directly (so the eggs steam gently in the oven and don’t turn brown).,Cover the eggs and the baking dish tightly with aluminum foil. Make sure the foil tents up so it doesn’t touch any of the eggs.,Lift one edge of the foil and pour in boiling water ⅓ way up the muffin tin and re-cover with foil.,Place the eggs in the oven for 13 minutes. Check to make sure the egg whites and yolks are both fully cooked.,Remove foil and muffin tin from baking dish and let cool.,With a thin knife, remove the egg yolks and egg whites from the tin. Set the egg whites aside.,In a bowl, combine the cooked egg yolks, Greek yogurt, relish, mustard, hot sauce, salt, and pepper. Mix with a fork until well combined.,Place the mixture in a piping bag with a desirable tip and pipe the yolk mixture onto the cooked egg whites. Sprinkle with paprika and chopped parsley.,Enjoy!,',NULL,'https://img.buzzfeed.com/thumbnailer-prod-us-east-1/video-api/assets/271531.jpg','protein:8;fat:6;calories:97;sugar:1;carbs:1;fiber:0',1596),
